Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.34,0:00:03.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1}{\fnArial Black\pos(316,325)\fad(400,0)}Obey the Rules and manners\Nto have a fun Duel!!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.30,0:00:16.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Worried that this full tank of energy will lose it's destination
Dialogue: 0,0:00:16.57,0:00:22.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Whoever shakes for just a minute their boredom, will explode!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:22.71,0:00:28.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I ride, atop the white line, Oh, Oh, Oh
Dialogue: 0,0:00:28.79,0:00:34.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Sit down, in the place you have faith Oh, Oh, Oh
Dialogue: 0,0:00:34.80,0:00:37.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Go to the place that tempts you!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:38.19,0:00:44.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}If each person took one thing at a time, freedom and passion in their hand
Dialogue: 0,0:00:44.45,0:00:50.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}For the shine to come, continue our journey
Dialogue: 0,0:00:50.59,0:00:56.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The unclear everyday trump-card that sustains me, is your soul
Dialogue: 0,0:00:56.78,0:01:02.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The best growth is coming forth, unstoppable wild drive
Dialogue: 0,0:01:02.84,0:01:08.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}We are both yet to settle down, striking the door
Dialogue: 0,0:01:17.93,0:01:19.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Just you wait, Honda!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:19.01,0:01:21.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I'll get your body back really soon!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:21.85,0:01:26.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}These Big Five creeps keep attacking us with different Deck Masters,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:26.64,0:01:30.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}But me and Yugi working as a team makes us invincible!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:30.98,0:01:34.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}But now that we've backed him into a corner,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:34.86,0:01:36.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}how can he be {\b0}laughing{\b1}?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:37.91,0:01:43.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Beat It! The Five God Dragon"
Dialogue: 0,0:01:49.75,0:01:52.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I've been {\i1}waiting{\i0} for this moment!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.21,0:01:56.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,For the third turn of which Altar of Mists was activated!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.13,0:01:57.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.09,0:02:00.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We've just {\i1}won{\i0} this Duel!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.47,0:02:03.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I activate the Effect of Altar of Mists!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.18,0:02:07.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I add Dragon Revival Ritual from my deck to my hand!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:07.10,0:02:14.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Dragon Revival Ritual is the necessary Ritual Magic Card used to Summon Five God Dragon.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.07,0:02:15.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What did you just say?!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.32,0:02:26.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,However, you must also sacrifice five Monster Cards consisting of the Earth, Water, Fire, Wind and Darkness Attributes.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.29,0:02:30.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There's no way you'd conveniently have all five of those Monster Attributes on hand at once!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.33,0:02:33.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I see you still haven't realized.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.71,0:02:35.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Take a close look behind me!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.17,0:02:40.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Behind you, you said...?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.34,0:02:43.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Psycho Shocker!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.14,0:02:44.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I get it!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.18,0:02:45.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Their Deck Masters!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.97,0:02:48.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If I remember right, Judge Man was an Earth-Attribute!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.77,0:02:51.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Deepsea Warrior was a Water-Attribute!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.15,0:02:54.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm pretty sure the Machine Sergeant was a Fire-Attribute.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.36,0:02:56.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Penguin Nightmare was\N a Wind-Attribute!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.57,0:03:01.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So then Psycho Shocker...|N is a Dark-Attribute?!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.36,0:03:03.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}You're all right!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.12,0:03:03.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}So here goes!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.95,0:03:05.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I Summon my Deck Master!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.74,0:03:08.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Android - Psycho Shocker!!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.58,0:03:12.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I Summon my Deck Master!\N Deepsea Warrior!!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.25,0:03:16.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I Summon my Deck Master!\N Penguin Nightmare!!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.55,0:03:19.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I Summon my Deck Master!\N Judge Man!!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.88,0:03:24.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I Summon my Deck Master!\N Machine Sergeant!!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.30,0:03:27.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I activate Dragon Revival Ritual!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.26,0:03:33.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I will now polymerize our Deck Masters consisting of Earth, Water, Fire, Wind and Darkness Attributes!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.23,0:03:35.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I then Summon the Five God Dragon!!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.04,0:03:49.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Five God Dragon!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.91,0:03:53.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Shit...! This thing caused us and Mai so many problems...!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.22,0:04:02.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}It's up to you...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.05,0:04:03.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Jounouchi-kun!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.22,0:04:07.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Jounouchi-{\i0}kun{\i1}...!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.64,0:04:08.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Jounouchi!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.72,0:04:10.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Jounouchi!!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.47,0:04:13.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This thing's gonna\N mop the floor with us!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.19,0:04:17.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This Monster cannot attack on the turn it's Summoned.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.07,0:04:20.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What the heck?\N Don't scare me like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.78,0:04:23.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But it {\i1}does{\i0} have the Effect
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.15,0:04:27.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,to destroy every Monster, Magic and Trap Card on the opponent's side of the field on the turn it's Summoned!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.96,0:04:39.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's low! Stop trying to throw our guard off!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.71,0:04:42.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I must {\i1}apologize{\i0} for that.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.59,0:04:45.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,To make up for it, let me give you a little forewarning.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.38,0:04:53.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Monsters of the Earth, Water, Fire, Wind and Darkness Attributes cannot damage the Five God Dragon!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.81,0:04:58.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then that means almost all Monsters' attacks won't work on it?!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.65,0:05:05.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}There's not a single soul who can defeat the Five God Dragon, the very unity of {\b0}ourselves{\b1}!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.99,0:05:09.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}However, we learned the hard way in our previous battle.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.28,0:05:12.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}As such, we're taking every needed precaution in this match.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.20,0:05:14.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I place a set card!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.37,0:05:17.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Turn over!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.17,0:05:19.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}What's the matter, Jounouchi?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.38,0:05:20.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}It's your turn, you know!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.59,0:05:24.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This ain't about what's wrong...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.34,0:05:29.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How the hell do we beat a Monster with 5000 Attack Points?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.22,0:05:30.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh, Yugi?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.01,0:05:33.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Just do your best, Jounouchi-{\i1}kun{\i0}!\N A chance will come sooner of later!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.56,0:05:35.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, you're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.77,0:05:37.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Heh, I better pull myself together.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.90,0:05:40.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I can't rely on Yugi all the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.40,0:05:41.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My turn!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.48,0:05:42.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Draw!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.98,0:05:47.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't have a Monster to Summon...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.40,0:05:50.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But I'll do what I have to do\N until the very end!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.66,0:05:53.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll place three reverse cards face-down on the field!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.79,0:05:58.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm counting on you, my Deck Master!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.75,0:06:01.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I Summon my Deck Master,\N Flame Swordsman!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.51,0:06:08.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Jounouchi! You'll {\i1}lose{\i0} if your Deck Master is beaten!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.59,0:06:12.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And if you lose, you'll end up looking like me, ooh~!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.14,0:06:13.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Big brother!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.31,0:06:17.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I just did everything I could.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.06,0:06:21.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Looks like I'll be relying on you in the end after all...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.57,0:06:26.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I guess all I can do is leave this to Yugi...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.57,0:06:28.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Turn over!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.24,0:06:31.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Let me handle this, Jounouchi-{\i0}kun{\i1}.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.32,0:06:33.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}We've still got a way to win.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.62,0:06:35.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My turn, draw!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.71,0:06:40.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I Summon my Deck Master!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.37,0:06:41.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Black Magician!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.17,0:06:48.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Not just Jounouchi, but even {\i1}Yugi{\i0} Summoned his Deck Master?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.38,0:06:50.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What in the world\N are those two thinking?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.51,0:06:54.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But if they don't have any Monsters on the field,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.68,0:06:58.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,they'd just get Direct Attacked, and Yugi and Jounouchi would be done for, ooh-ah~!!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.43,0:07:03.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There's no method in existence that can beat the Five God Dragon!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.77,0:07:07.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How about you spare your dignity and just surrender now before you lost miserably?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.07,0:07:10.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yugi...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.49,0:07:18.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Only shame awaits those who talk big without the efficiency to back up their words.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.08,0:07:19.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What did you say?!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.75,0:07:25.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's not like you guys are the only ones who can fuse their Deck Masters!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.92,0:07:26.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.88,0:07:27.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Fuse?!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.21,0:07:32.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}D-Don't tell me he's about to play Master of Dragon Knight again!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.56,0:07:44.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}No! He shouldn't be able to play Master of Dragon Knight without the Blue-Eyes!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.23,0:07:50.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I fuse our Deck Masters together!\N Black Magician and Flame Swordsman!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.19,0:07:54.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,As a result, I Fusion Summon the knight of black fire, Black Flare Knight!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.09,0:08:16.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,B-Black Flare Knight, you said?!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.14,0:08:19.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This card is able to attack on the same turn it is polymerized!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.43,0:08:23.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then go ahead and try your luck!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.23,0:08:25.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That Monster is a Dark-Attribute.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.40,0:08:28.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sure I {\i1}told you{\i0} they don't work on the Five God Dragon!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.23,0:08:36.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That aside, you actually plan to attack a 5000 Attack Power Monster with a Monster only holding 2200 Attack Points?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.87,0:08:38.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You bet I am!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.99,0:08:40.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What was that?!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.12,0:08:43.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wouldn't that mean he'd be killing himself for nothing?!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.33,0:08:44.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's {\i1}suicidal{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.96,0:08:46.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, Yugi-{\i1}kun{\i0}'s got this right!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.92,0:08:49.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I know he's planning something!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.17,0:08:52.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I don't really get what he's hoping to accomplish...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.34,0:08:54.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}But I trust Yugi!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.84,0:09:00.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I use the knight of black fire, Black Flare Knight, to attack the Five God Dragon!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.35,0:09:08.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Have you lost your mind, Yugi?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.03,0:09:21.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why?! Why hasn't your Life changed?!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.99,0:09:26.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Regardless of how many Attack Points a Monster has that's attacked by this card,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.12,0:09:29.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,even if that Attack happens to be higher than its own,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.79,0:09:32.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,the player will not receive any damage!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.17,0:09:37.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's all a part of the knight of black fire's, Black Flare Knight's, Special Effect!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.22,0:09:38.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.14,0:09:39.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And that's not all.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.60,0:09:42.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The moment this card is destroyed,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.01,0:09:47.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can Special Summon Illusion Knight - Mirage Knight from my hand or deck!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.69,0:09:56.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And so what if you can?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.90,0:10:02.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Even if slightly higher, this Monster still hardly holds enough Attack Power to scrap the Five God Dragon's foot!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.95,0:10:07.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Unless this is {\i1}also{\i0}\N a Special Effect Monster?!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.12,0:10:12.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Illusion Knight - Mirage Knight, attack Five God Dragon!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.80,0:10:23.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Illusion Knight cannot be destroyed in battle!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.68,0:10:31.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And during Damage Calculation, the Attack Power of the Monster being attacked is added to its own!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.94,0:10:39.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Meaning the 5000 Attack Points of the one being attacked, Five God Dragon, will be added to the Illusion Knight's own!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.57,0:10:45.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I-Impossible! 7800 Attack Points?!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.49,0:10:48.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And let me give you some last bit of information.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.54,0:10:51.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Illusion Knight - Mirage Knight is a Light-Attribute!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.96,0:10:56.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The only Monsters that can successfully attack the Five God Dragon are creatures of light!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.38,0:11:01.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,From darkness to light!\N I've been waiting for this moment!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.89,0:11:12.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We beat the Five God Dragon!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.27,0:11:16.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That means the 2800 points in difference will be subtracted from your Life Points!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.69,0:11:18.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Your Life is now at zero!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.32,0:11:21.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We've just won this Duel!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.66,0:11:27.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?! Why didn't your\N Life Points drop to 0?!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.08,0:11:29.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What the hell is the deal?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.71,0:11:31.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Did you cheat again somehow?!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.05,0:11:41.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It seems my strategy was one step ahead of yours.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.34,0:11:44.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Take a nice, long look at my field!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.22,0:11:44.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What!?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.01,0:11:47.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Bargaining with Demons!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.89,0:11:48.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Correct.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.89,0:11:53.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's a Trap Card that can only be activated when a Level 8 or higher Monster on my side of the field is destroyed!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.98,0:12:01.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This Trap negates all damage I received to 0 at the cost of half of my Life Points.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.90,0:12:05.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So that's why your Life Points didn't drop to zero?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.03,0:12:08.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And that's not all.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.87,0:12:13.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When this Trap is activated, I can Summon Berserk Dead Dragon!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.78,0:12:43.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? The Illusion Knight\N returned to normal.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.45,0:12:51.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Once the Battle Phase ends, the Illusion Knight is destroyed, and Black Magician and Flame Swordsman are Special Summoned.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.62,0:12:55.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh no! Once that Big Five guy takes his next turn,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.42,0:13:00.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yugi-{\i1}kun{\i0}'s and Jounouchi-{\i1}kun{\i0}'s Deck Masters will be wiped out!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.00,0:13:02.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Does that mean they'll lose, ooh-ah?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.09,0:13:04.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That can't be!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.13,0:13:06.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Please! Keep trying, big brother!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.47,0:13:08.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Say "keep trying" all you want...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.85,0:13:11.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's Yugi's turn right now, ya know!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.14,0:13:12.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We're countin' on you, Yugi!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.77,0:13:17.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I activate the Magic Card, Magical Silk Hats!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.57,0:13:23.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Also, my Deck Master Ability!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.24,0:13:24.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Separate Magic!!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.65,0:13:31.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,By paying 1000 Life Points, I am permitted to use the Effects of the Magic Card, Magical Silk Hats, once again!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.33,0:13:37.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Turn over!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.71,0:13:40.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Nice one, Yugi!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.09,0:13:42.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now we've at least got a chance.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.09,0:13:45.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, we've just delayed the inevitable.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.09,0:13:46.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We can't relax just yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.84,0:13:48.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Heh, relax! We're fine!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.76,0:13:50.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He can't handle this!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.68,0:13:55.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I get that feeling way\N more than you think.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.64,0:14:00.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But reality often steals away the last bit of hope we hold dear.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.73,0:14:02.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My turn! Draw!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.57,0:14:06.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let me explain.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.45,0:14:15.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Berserk Dead Dragon holds a Special Ability that allows it to attack four Monsters every time it attacks.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.25,0:14:17.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,E-Every time it attacks?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.96,0:14:19.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Four Monsters?!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.63,0:14:26.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yugi has the Black Magician hidden under four Magical Silk Hats on his side.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.09,0:14:30.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And Jounouchi-{\i1}kun{\i0} has the Flame Swordsman hidden on his!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.05,0:14:37.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So if he attacks either Yugi or Jounouchi, who both have four hats on the field...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.73,0:14:39.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's a 100% failure rate!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.73,0:14:40.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That means...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.69,0:14:45.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,On this turn, either Jounouchi-{\i1}kun{\i0} or myself will be defeated.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.11,0:14:47.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No! We still don't know that!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.28,0:14:48.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What the hell are you talking about?!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.95,0:14:49.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you an idiot?!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.95,0:14:52.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He's always sucked at math, ooh-ah~!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.41,0:14:57.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then allow me to show you first hand!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.54,0:15:02.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, after your {\i1}friend's{\i0} loss, that is.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.92,0:15:09.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I use Berserk Dragon to attack all four of Yugi Mutou's silk hats at once!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.77,0:15:18.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is this the end...?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.02,0:15:19.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't give up, Yugi!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.94,0:15:24.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Flame Swordsman!\N Protect Black Magician! Protect {\i1}Yugi{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.48,0:15:25.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Jounouchi-{\i1}kun{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.86,0:15:28.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's way too reckless, Jounouchi-{\i1}kun{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.53,0:15:31.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If he does that, Jounouchi will lose!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.45,0:15:32.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't do it, big brother!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.91,0:15:35.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let {\i1}me{\i0} be the monkey, OOH~!!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.80,0:15:50.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Jounouchi-{\i1}kun{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.14,0:15:56.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-Jounouchi!\n-Jounouchi-{\i1}kun{\i0}!\N -Big brother!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.51,0:15:57.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.31,0:15:58.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Impossible!\N Huh...?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.94,0:16:07.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.07,0:16:09.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why is the Flame Swordsman still alive?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.61,0:16:12.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Because {\i1}this{\i0} thing saved my butt!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.16,0:16:15.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,One Dollar Silver Coin...?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.87,0:16:22.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's right! This activates only when I receive battle damage after you attack a Monster with 1000 or less Attack Points!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.04,0:16:25.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This Trap Card makes\N all the damage invalid!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.71,0:16:28.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,1000 Attack Points...?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.17,0:16:29.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now I get it!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.84,0:16:33.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Flame Swordsman has 1800 Attack Points.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.26,0:16:38.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But you reduced his Attack Power by 1000 points in order to use his Deck Master Ability!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.18,0:16:41.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's why your Trap was activated!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.44,0:16:47.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Great job thinking so far ahead like that, Jounouchi-{\i1}kun{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.11,0:16:50.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now we're even!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.44,0:16:52.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now what're ya gonna do, Big Five guy?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.99,0:16:57.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Damn it all! Just how much are you gonna piss me off?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.07,0:16:58.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My turn's over!!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.87,0:17:03.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? Its Attack Power dropped.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.29,0:17:10.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Berserk Dead Dragon's Attack Power drops by 500 points at the end of your turn!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.59,0:17:13.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh wow! That sucks for {\i1}you{\i0}, man!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.76,0:17:14.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My turn!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.88,0:17:16.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Draw!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.93,0:17:20.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Magic Card, open!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.10,0:17:21.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I activate Knight's Title!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.68,0:17:27.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This automatically turns Yugi's Black Magician into a Warrior-Type!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.32,0:17:41.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And now for Flame Swordsman's Deck Master Ability!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.37,0:17:44.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I transfer 700 of its Attack Points!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.63,0:17:53.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He's got 3200 Attack Points!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.21,0:17:56.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So he's stronger\N than Berserk Dead Dragon?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.30,0:17:58.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's all I can do for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.64,0:18:00.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The rest is up to you, Yugi!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.60,0:18:01.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.77,0:18:03.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Turn over!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.97,0:18:09.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks, Jounouchi-{\i1}kun{\i0}! I couldn't have won this Duel without you!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.27,0:18:11.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey! What's the meaning of this, Ouka?!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.57,0:18:14.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I thought you said Jounouchi would hold him {\i1}back{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.15,0:18:17.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't he making Yugi more {\i1}powerful{\i0}?!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.24,0:18:20.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,T-This wasn't supposed to...!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.41,0:18:21.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's my last turn!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.99,0:18:22.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Draw!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.83,0:18:30.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Here goes! I use the Warrior of Black Magic - Black Magician's Knight, to attack Berserk Dead Dragon!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.06,0:18:50.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Berserk Dead Dragon is beaten!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.94,0:18:57.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Big Five! Your Deck Master was destroyed!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.40,0:19:01.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That means we've won this Duel!!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.78,0:19:03.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We lost...!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.16,0:19:07.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They did it! Yugi and Jounouchi won!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.79,0:19:09.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You did great, big brother!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.83,0:19:13.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Honda-{\i1}kun{\i0}! Now you can get your body back!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.34,0:19:14.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you, Yugi!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.75,0:19:15.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you, Jounouchi!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.47,0:19:24.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now return Honda-{\i1}kun{\i0}'s body just as you promised.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.93,0:19:29.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If this is the case, we'll be taking your bodies by force!!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.39,0:19:32.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's not fair, you jerks!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.12,0:19:46.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's the meaning of this?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.74,0:19:48.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}You're really sad, Big Five!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.83,0:19:50.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Noah-{\i0}sama{\i1}!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.37,0:19:52.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Your job here is done.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.67,0:19:59.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They disappeared...!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.59,0:20:02.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's so cruel...! After they won the Duel, too...!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.76,0:20:05.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,N-No way, ooh...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.64,0:20:10.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll never look like a human being again, ooh-ah~!!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.31,0:20:14.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is this the end for me, ooh-ah, OOH-AH~!?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.94,0:20:19.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm so sorry, Honda-{\i1}san{\i0}...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.36,0:20:22.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That may not be so bad after all, ooh~
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.12,0:20:28.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Noah-{\i1}sama{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.04,0:20:30.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can't stand looking at losers.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.95,0:20:33.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't you agree, Mokuba?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.46,0:20:35.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Losers will never win, regardless of what they do!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.71,0:20:39.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Honda's body is gone!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.67,0:20:41.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That can't be! When did it happen?!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.42,0:20:46.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Noah-{\i1}sama{\i0}, just once more!\N Please just grant us one more chance!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.64,0:20:50.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We just want a real human body, no matter what it takes!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.35,0:20:52.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We beg of you, Noah-{\i1}sama{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.52,0:20:54.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Just give us {\i1}one more chance{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.56,0:21:04.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Did you fools {\i1}really{\i0} believe you'd get real bodies if you won that Duel back there?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.70,0:21:07.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What did you say just now...?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.12,0:21:10.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let me put it another way...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.54,0:21:15.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There's not a {\i1}real{\i0} thing {\i1}here{\i0} in this Virtual World!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.21,0:21:18.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can't believe it!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.50,0:21:21.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-YOU DECEIVED US!!\N -HOW DARE YOU, NOAH!?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.55,0:21:24.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,SCREW YOU TO HELL!!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.68,0:21:28.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's because you guys\N were to stupid to realize!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.86,0:21:44.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Even though we defeated the Big Five, we're still trapped inside this Virtual Space!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.24,0:21:47.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In this case, we've got no other choice but to go talk to Noah directly.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:48.74,0:21:51.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kaiba-{\i1}kun{\i0} has already started to fight against Noah!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:51.87,0:21:55.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Noah explains the secrets behind his Creation of Heaven and Earth Deck.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:55.50,0:21:59.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And how Noah is related to Kaiba-{\i1}kun{\i0}...!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:59.17,0:21:59.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Next time!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:59.75,0:22:02.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Noah VS Seto: Duel of the Creation of Heaven and Earth"
Dialogue: 0,0:22:02.96,0:22:04.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Duel standby!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:06.87,0:22:14.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The unsinkable sun, wherever it rises
Dialogue: 0,0:22:14.78,0:22:23.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}A dream is a dream, and it won't stop
Dialogue: 0,0:22:24.05,0:22:28.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The straight rail and the steep route
Dialogue: 0,0:22:28.73,0:22:33.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}To go, or not go all of yourself
Dialogue: 0,0:22:33.12,0:22:40.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I'm getting tired of counting my advances in a cage
Dialogue: 0,0:22:40.68,0:22:44.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Respect! Boys, show me your strength
Dialogue: 0,0:22:44.27,0:22:49.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}It's awkward, but draw the map
Dialogue: 0,0:22:49.04,0:22:59.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Now let's walk forever with our head up high...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:59.19,0:23:07.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The unsinkable sun, if it starts to get to familiar like you
Dialogue: 0,0:23:07.00,0:23:15.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}answer freely to the everyday discomfort
Dialogue: 0,0:23:15.78,0:23:23.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I want to believe you, because I am losing my way with everything
Dialogue: 0,0:23:23.76,0:23:33.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Hiding in my heart... this secret paradise
